    title: 'Web Developer',
    description: '\u003cp\u003eCrawford, Murphy \u0026amp; Tilly, Inc. (CMT) is a civil engineering and consulting firm that provides web applications for our clients. We are seeking an outstanding Web Developer to be responsible for the coding, innovative design, and layout of our client-facing websites and web applications. This role will engage in creating and modifying web pages to function while following a specific branding schema. The selected candidate will strive to create visually appealing applications that feature user-friendly design and clear navigation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOther responsibilities include integrating data from various back-end services and databases (primarily SQL) and creating website layout/user interface using standard HTML/CSS practices. Some applications will use GIS integration, although this experience is not required as we have in-house expertise.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePosition Requirements:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA bachelor’s degree in CIS, MIS, IT, or related field or equivalent work experience\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e3 to 5 years of Web Development experience\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDeep expertise and hands-on experience with Web Applications and programming languages such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript, JQuery, and API’s\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDeep functional knowledge or hands-on design experience with Web Services (REST, SOAP, etc.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExperience with reactive design for various formats such as tablets or mobile devices\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eStrong grasp of security principles\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAbility to manage multiple tasks and meet deadlines\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHighly self-motivated, resourceful, with ability to work under pressure\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWilling to learn new technologies and engage in growing CMT’s capabilities\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eClose proximity to a CMT office is preferred – Eastern or Central time zone preferred\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCandidates interested in applying should provide a summary of previous experience including examples of your web design capabilities (active websites).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCMT is committed to individual opportunity and the professional development of our employees.  This position offers an opportunity to take that next step helping reach your career goals and personal potential.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCMT is committed to diversity, equity, and inclusion.  CMT is an Equal Opportunity Employer and employment selection decisions are based on merit, qualifications, and abilities. CMT does not discriminate in employment opportunities or practices on the basis of age, color, disability, gender identity, national origin, race, religion, sex, sexual orientation, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by country, regional or local law. Please note that CMT does not accept unsolicited resumes from recruiters or employment agencies.\u003c/p\u003e\n',
    how_to_apply: '\u003cp\u003ePlease apply on our Careers Page: \u003ca href="https://www.cmtengr.com/posted-positions-2/"\u003ehttps://www.cmtengr.com/posted-positions-2/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n',
