    location: 'Fort Worth, TX (Remote)',
    title: 'Front End Software Engineer',
    description: '\u003cp\u003eThis job is fully remote.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBuxton is the leader in customer intelligence solutions and technology. We use science to identify, track, measure, and predict everything about customer behavior all over the globe. We build technology that makes this customer intelligence easily accessible to our clients, empowering them to make the best growth investments possible.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe are a trusted partner for many of the most well-respected, healthcare, retail, restaurant, private equity, financial services, hospitality, city government, property owner, developer, and broker companies across the US and internationally.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBuxton is seeking a passionate, heavy-hitting, Front-End Software Engineer to join our team. In this important role, you will join a strong and energized Agile team utilizing the latest and greatest in cutting edge technology to make a measurable impact on our organization.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Front-End Software Engineer is a solid, positive, and innovative individual who thrives in a group with a small-team but big-ideas mentality and a lot of meaningful collaboration between engineers, product managers, and designers. Working on projects that are the lifeblood of the organization, your confidence and background in system architecture and coding in full platform build outs will allow you to thrive in a culture that supports you and your ideas.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat you’ll do\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBuild robust and scalable software in a major programming language like React, Angular, etc.\nDesign and create services and system architecture for your projects and contribute and provide feedback to other team members.\nHelp improve our code quality through writing unit tests, automation and performing code reviews.\nParticipate in brainstorming sessions and contribute ideas to our technology, algorithms and products.\nDive into difficult problems and successfully deliver results on schedule.\nWork with the product and design teams to understand end-user requirements, formulate use cases, and then translate that into a pragmatic and effective technical solution.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat you’ll bring\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBachelor’s degree in computer science or related discipline is preferred.\n3+ years of experience with React, Angular, or Vue.\nProven experience in building complex SaaS web applications.\nPractical and significant hands-on experience with ReactJS, component composition, and functional language practice.\nA track record of projects completed on time – you are a flawless executor, not a procrastinator.\nExcellent understanding of UI Frameworks and how best to tackle multiple client requests.\nSolid knowledge of JavaScript and related frameworks for use within the application and to create effective UI interaction.\nPreferably, basic SQL Experience (DML, DDL, SQL Tuning, etc - Preferably SQL Server).\nPreferably, 1+ years of experience with Geospatial analysis and Big Data topics.\nPreferably, 1+ years of experience with one or more Cloud providers (AWS is preferred).\nPreferably, 2+ years of experience with client-side testing experience and devops integration.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBenefits\nHealth Care Plan (Medical, Dental \u0026amp; Vision)\nRetirement Plan (401k, IRA)\nLife Insurance (Basic, Voluntary \u0026amp; AD\u0026amp;D)\nGenerous Paid Time Off\nShort Term \u0026amp; Long-Term Disability\nTraining \u0026amp; Development\nRemote-first Culture\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere at Buxton, we believe strongly that we benefit from diversity and encourage applicants from underrepresented backgrounds to apply. We value inclusion and welcome diverse viewpoints. Upon hire, a successful background check is required. Unfortunately, we are unable to sponsor work visas at this time.\u003c/p\u003e\n',
    how_to_apply: '\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href="https://apply.workable.com/buxton/j/459379C2CB/"\u003ehttps://apply.workable.com/buxton/j/459379C2CB/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n',
